1
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:39,280
Yujiao, please accept my condolences.

2
00:01:39,280 --> 00:01:41,009
Take care of your health first.

3
00:01:42,520 --> 00:01:43,400
Rest assured.

4
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:45,800
As for Huaiyi's funeral arrangements,

5
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:48,560
I will do my utmost.

6
00:01:49,520 --> 00:01:50,360
Adjutant Liu.

7
00:01:50,560 --> 00:01:51,560
After you, Madam.

8
00:02:19,640 --> 00:02:20,600
Yunkui.

9
00:02:21,320 --> 00:02:22,760
It is only fair and reasonable

10
00:02:22,760 --> 00:02:24,120
that everything the Party and State owes you

11
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:25,450
will be paid back to you.

12
00:02:25,840 --> 00:02:27,600
As long as you insist on reversing the verdict,

13
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:29,720
it's my duty to help.

14
00:02:41,560 --> 00:02:42,880
Deputy Minister Huang,

15
00:02:42,880 --> 00:02:44,840
that scene just now was truly sincere

16
00:02:44,840 --> 00:02:45,900
and very touching.

17
00:02:46,079 --> 00:02:48,000
I believe Mrs. Sun wasn't acting.

18
00:02:48,560 --> 00:02:49,800
But I also believe

19
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:52,420
there must be a director behind this.

20
00:02:54,880 --> 00:02:56,320
I won't deny that.

21
00:02:57,880 --> 00:02:59,560
The Japanese Army has occupied Xuzhou.

22
00:02:59,560 --> 00:03:02,600
Their next step is to advance west along both banks of the Yangtze River.

23
00:03:02,600 --> 00:03:04,960
At this critical moment of life and death for the Chinese nation,

24
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:06,760
every high-ranking general who dies for the country

25
00:03:06,760 --> 00:03:08,290
will be a spiritual banner.

26
00:03:08,640 --> 00:03:11,370
A hero who just covered the main force's breakout

27
00:03:11,440 --> 00:03:13,640
suddenly turning into a villain who framed his comrades

28
00:03:13,640 --> 00:03:15,700
and delayed military operations...

29
00:03:15,720 --> 00:03:18,200
This banner will inevitably become

30
00:03:18,320 --> 00:03:20,600
a laughable and great irony.

31
00:03:21,600 --> 00:03:22,760
What I just said

32
00:03:23,320 --> 00:03:25,380
is what you wanted to say to me, right?

33
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:26,240
So,

34
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:28,900
the Military Commission wants me to give up.

35
00:03:29,160 --> 00:03:30,360
Am I right?

36
00:03:31,160 --> 00:03:32,360
Yunkui, my friend.

37
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:35,460
That's not entirely true.

38
00:03:36,280 --> 00:03:39,120
The Military Commission will privately allocate special funds

39
00:03:39,120 --> 00:03:41,120
for all the officers and soldiers of the 87th Brigade,

40
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:43,720
according to the treatment of fallen martyrs,

41
00:03:44,320 --> 00:03:45,720
to distribute pensions.

42
00:03:46,079 --> 00:03:48,040
As for your parents, wife, and children,

43
00:03:48,040 --> 00:03:51,880
they will also be compensated according to the standards of a lieutenant general.

44
00:03:51,880 --> 00:03:52,610
Don't worry.

45
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:55,880
I will take full responsibility for all of this.

46
00:03:57,120 --> 00:03:58,560
If you insist on suing,

47
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:06,090
I will submit all the files tonight

48
00:04:06,240 --> 00:04:07,700
to Generalissimo Chiang.

49
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:09,680
What course to follow

50
00:04:10,720 --> 00:04:12,080
is entirely up to you.

51
00:04:12,480 --> 00:04:14,280
No need, Deputy Minister Huang.

52
00:04:14,880 --> 00:04:15,840
I appreciate

53
00:04:16,440 --> 00:04:17,720
your kindness.

54
00:04:18,519 --> 00:04:20,120
I remember Lu Yun once told me

55
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:23,140
that we are never the ones to change history.

56
00:04:23,520 --> 00:04:25,240
We can only endure history.

57
00:04:25,880 --> 00:04:27,360
I didn't profoundly realize this

58
00:04:27,360 --> 00:04:29,360
until today.

59
00:04:30,240 --> 00:04:31,570
Compared to Sun Huaiyi,

60
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:33,920
I hate the Japanese more.

61
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:35,520
If my silence

62
00:04:35,960 --> 00:04:37,960
can help stabilize military morale

63
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,080
and ensure soldiers' obedience...

64
00:04:39,080 --> 00:04:39,960
Fine.

65
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:42,280
Then I will accept the Military Commission's arrangement.

66
00:04:42,280 --> 00:04:43,320
I accept it.

67
00:04:49,960 --> 00:04:51,120
Yunkui.

68
00:04:53,520 --> 00:04:54,920
Whatever plans you have,

69
00:04:55,320 --> 00:04:57,560
I can suggest them to Minister He for arrangement.

70
00:04:57,560 --> 00:04:58,640
I will disappear.

71
00:04:59,840 --> 00:05:01,770
Isn't that what the Party and State

72
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:03,890
wants to see the most right now?

73
00:05:04,320 --> 00:05:05,600
Yunkui.

74
00:05:07,480 --> 00:05:09,880
Rest and recuperate for a year or two first.

75
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:11,840
Even Liao Fengnian thought

76
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:13,640
you and Pang Zhonghao had already

77
00:05:13,640 --> 00:05:15,040
died in battle in Xuzhou.

78
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:21,000
How many absurd things are there in this world?

79
00:05:22,280 --> 00:05:24,880
We have no control over our advance or retreat.

80
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:26,920
Harboring lofty ambitions in vain.

81
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:30,360
A heart of ice,

82
00:05:31,880 --> 00:05:34,200
who can I tell?

83
00:05:55,640 --> 00:05:56,970
Deputy Minister Huang.

84
00:05:58,200 --> 00:05:59,680
I am wearing a long gown,

85
00:06:00,400 --> 00:06:02,360
and cannot salute you.

86
00:06:22,280 --> 00:06:23,160
Yueming.

87
00:06:23,640 --> 00:06:24,960
For over half a year,

88
00:06:24,960 --> 00:06:27,840
your father Yunkui fought through mountains of corpses and seas of blood,

89
00:06:27,840 --> 00:06:29,480
just to clear the names

90
00:06:29,480 --> 00:06:31,120
of his brothers.

91
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:34,680
But the Nationalist Government, to cover up for the higher-ups,

92
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:37,480
used the pensions of his 6,000 brothers as bargaining chips

93
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:40,440
to force him to keep quiet and disappear,

94
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:43,000
completely abandoning them.

95
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:47,400
His trust collapsed amidst the shifting of blame,

96
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:50,400
and from then on, he lost faith in the KMT.

97
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:52,760
When the door of the old world

98
00:06:52,760 --> 00:06:54,640
slammed shut,

99
00:06:54,960 --> 00:06:57,960
another door opened.

100
00:06:58,600 --> 00:07:00,880
He finally could clearly see

101
00:07:01,080 --> 00:07:02,800
the powerful strength

102
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:04,920
of those resistance forces rooted in the people

103
00:07:04,920 --> 00:07:08,240
and united from top to bottom.

104
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:10,680
Inject Prontosil for bed one and bed two.

105
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:12,360
Debride and then bandage bed three.

106
00:07:12,360 --> 00:07:14,040
Pay special attention to these three beds.

107
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:15,000
If the wounds get bigger,

108
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:15,960
increase the dose of anti-inflammatory drugs.

109
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:16,490
Zuliang.

110
00:07:16,840 --> 00:07:17,720
I've passed all my assessments.

111
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:18,840
Shuzhen, that's great.

112
00:07:18,840 --> 00:07:21,120
The instructor said I can come to the ward for internship.

113
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:21,720
Let me try.

114
00:07:21,920 --> 00:07:22,440
Okay.

115
00:07:22,720 --> 00:07:24,120
Xiaoyue, what about you?

116
00:07:24,640 --> 00:07:25,760
The instructor said

117
00:07:25,760 --> 00:07:27,620
I need to study for a while longer.

118
00:07:27,680 --> 00:07:29,840
Today I'm just accompanying Her Ladyship to take a look.

119
00:07:29,840 --> 00:07:30,520
Okay.

120
00:07:31,080 --> 00:07:32,200
Since you're here,

121
00:07:32,560 --> 00:07:33,600
why don't you broaden your horizons?

122
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:34,320
Come along.

123
00:07:34,640 --> 00:07:35,440
Okay.

124
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:37,040
Come.

125
00:07:37,760 --> 00:07:38,560
Dr. Luo, let me help you.

126
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:39,159
Sign here.

127
00:07:40,720 --> 00:07:41,600
Okay, come.

128
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:43,320
Let's go.

129
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:44,000
Okay.

130
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:49,690
High body temperature.

131
00:07:51,760 --> 00:07:52,760
Wound infection.

132
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:54,120
Skin peeled back,

133
00:07:54,440 --> 00:07:55,560
continuous local bleeding,

134
00:07:55,560 --> 00:07:56,560
irregular edges.

135
00:07:58,200 --> 00:07:59,260
Sharp tenderness.

136
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:03,480
Inject Prontosil.

137
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:05,760
Shuzhen,

138
00:08:07,080 --> 00:08:08,120
can you do it?

139
00:08:09,760 --> 00:08:10,320
I can.

140
00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:10,960
Come.

141
00:08:19,840 --> 00:08:21,600
Step one, disinfect first.

142
00:08:22,920 --> 00:08:25,360
Step two, two fast and one slow.

143
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:27,890
Insert the needle fast,

144
00:08:28,440 --> 00:08:29,770
push the medicine slow.

145
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:34,280
Step three,

146
00:08:34,440 --> 00:08:36,570
press a cotton swab on the needle hole.

147
00:08:37,039 --> 00:08:38,799
Step two, two fast and one slow.

148
00:08:39,039 --> 00:08:40,640
Insert the needle fast, push the medicine slow.

149
00:08:40,640 --> 00:08:43,159
Insert the needle fast, push the medicine slow.

150
00:08:43,159 --> 00:08:45,080
Insert the needle fast, push the medicine slow.

151
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:46,520
Step one, disinfect first.

152
00:08:46,520 --> 00:08:47,780
No, it's already done.

153
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:50,360
Step two, two fast and one slow.

154
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:52,240
Don't be nervous.

155
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:53,330
I'm not nervous.

156
00:08:53,760 --> 00:08:54,760
You are.

157
00:08:57,400 --> 00:08:58,760
I'm not nervous.

158
00:09:00,920 --> 00:09:01,960
One,

159
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:03,840
two.

160
00:09:04,160 --> 00:09:05,080
Three.

161
00:09:05,880 --> 00:09:08,040
Zuliang, I can't do it.

162
00:09:08,640 --> 00:09:09,880
I've only practiced on pigskin.

163
00:09:09,880 --> 00:09:11,440
Never on a human being.

164
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:16,920
Hand.

165
00:09:20,880 --> 00:09:21,760
Step three,

166
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:24,020
press the cotton swab on the pinhole.

167
00:09:24,560 --> 00:09:25,320
Okay.

168
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:26,840
Step three,

169
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:28,800
press the cotton swab on the pinhole.

170
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:30,160
Step four, pull it out quickly.

171
00:09:30,160 --> 00:09:31,290
Pull it out quickly.

172
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:32,160
Dr. Luo,

173
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:34,640
two amputations need to be done at the same time.

174
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:35,480
We need you there.

175
00:09:35,480 --> 00:09:36,280
I'll be right there.

176
00:09:36,280 --> 00:09:37,410
Nurse Sun, let's go.

177
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:38,240
Shuzhen.

178
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:41,460
Xiaoyue, Shuzhen,

179
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:44,640
help us look after the wounded, okay?

180
00:09:44,640 --> 00:09:45,280
Okay.

181
00:09:45,680 --> 00:09:46,400
Let's go.

182
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:50,800
S-sorry.

183
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,260
It's my first time.

184
00:09:52,640 --> 00:09:54,300
I can see it's your first time.

185
00:09:55,080 --> 00:09:55,760
Nurse!

186
00:09:56,160 --> 00:09:56,880
Nurse!

187
00:09:57,400 --> 00:09:58,460
It's so itchy here.

188
00:09:58,800 --> 00:10:00,120
Take a look at it for me, quickly.

189
00:10:00,120 --> 00:10:00,920
It's so itchy!

190
00:10:08,080 --> 00:10:08,680
My lady.

191
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:10,760
Help me, quick.

192
00:10:12,640 --> 00:10:14,400
Here, drink some water.

193
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:15,920
It's so itchy.

194
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:19,960
Help me.

195
00:10:26,280 --> 00:10:27,200
Nurse,

196
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:31,160
help me.

197
00:10:31,160 --> 00:10:31,800
My lady.

198
00:10:31,800 --> 00:10:33,800
Nurse, what should I do if you leave?

199
00:10:41,560 --> 00:10:42,600
Help me, quick.

200
00:10:52,920 --> 00:10:53,840
Bear with it.

201
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:56,160
Bear with it.

202
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:09,320
Bear with it.

203
00:11:17,280 --> 00:11:18,680
Once the bugs are removed

204
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:21,440
and the medicine is applied, you'll be fine soon.

205
00:11:21,440 --> 00:11:22,440
Thank you, Nurse.

206
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:35,240
Shuzhen, it's okay.

207
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:36,800
I threw up my first time too.

208
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:40,060
Just now, when I lifted that wounded soldier's clothes...

209
00:11:46,560 --> 00:11:47,760
You'll get used to it.

210
00:11:49,480 --> 00:11:50,440
I tried.

211
00:11:50,880 --> 00:11:53,360
When washing gauze at the Shanghai field hospital,

212
00:11:53,360 --> 00:11:55,160
I went back and threw up for days.

213
00:11:56,120 --> 00:11:57,040
Zuliang,

214
00:11:57,560 --> 00:11:59,760
I have nightmares every night now.

215
00:12:00,280 --> 00:12:01,080
People I know,

216
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:02,610
people I don't know.

217
00:12:02,920 --> 00:12:04,050
They're either dead

218
00:12:04,080 --> 00:12:05,520
or dying.

219
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:07,640
I thought working with you

220
00:12:08,160 --> 00:12:10,020
would make me forget everything.

221
00:12:12,480 --> 00:12:13,340
How about this?

222
00:12:13,720 --> 00:12:14,650
Go home right now

223
00:12:14,760 --> 00:12:15,760
and get a good rest,

224
00:12:15,760 --> 00:12:16,400
okay?

225
00:12:16,440 --> 00:12:18,100
The house was bombed long ago.

226
00:12:18,640 --> 00:12:19,960
I have to squeeze into one room

227
00:12:19,960 --> 00:12:21,680
with your parents at the hotel.

228
00:12:21,680 --> 00:12:23,600
I don't even dare to turn over at night.

229
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:25,720
Shuzhen, everything is temporary.

230
00:12:26,280 --> 00:12:27,810
If you really can't hold on,

231
00:12:27,880 --> 00:12:29,680
go to Chongqing with my parents.

232
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:31,760
But the Japanese will chase us all the way

233
00:12:31,760 --> 00:12:33,080
and bomb Chongqing.

234
00:12:34,280 --> 00:12:36,920
Zuliang, come to Hong Kong with me.

235
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:38,320
Let's find my father.

236
00:12:38,480 --> 00:12:39,240
Hurry, hurry.

237
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:40,120
Hold on.

238
00:12:40,800 --> 00:12:42,680
Be careful. We're almost there.

239
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:45,050
Hurry up. Hang in there.

240
00:12:46,560 --> 00:12:47,690
We're almost there.

241
00:12:49,600 --> 00:12:50,730
Look at the wounded.

242
00:12:51,120 --> 00:12:53,850
Their legs are blown off, their stomachs busted.

243
00:12:55,280 --> 00:12:58,160
I don't want you to end up like them.

244
00:13:00,680 --> 00:13:01,920
Shuzhen.

245
00:13:02,840 --> 00:13:04,320
I am a military doctor.

246
00:13:04,920 --> 00:13:06,720
The Japanese are marching west.

247
00:13:06,920 --> 00:13:09,560
More and more wounded are sent from the frontline.

248
00:13:09,560 --> 00:13:11,220
As long as the war doesn't end,

249
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:14,800
the hospital is my battlefield.

250
00:13:16,080 --> 00:13:18,280
Dr. Luo, we need to prepare for surgery.

251
00:13:18,520 --> 00:13:19,650
I'll be right there.

252
00:13:21,960 --> 00:13:22,920
Shuzhen.

253
00:13:23,760 --> 00:13:24,620
Think about it.

254
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:25,680
We'll talk later.

255
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:46,640
Miss.

256
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:49,240
Are you okay?

257
00:14:28,880 --> 00:14:30,440
Stop looking.

258
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:32,640
It's here.

259
00:14:32,640 --> 00:14:33,440
Please help.

260
00:14:33,560 --> 00:14:35,040
Here, there's more.

261
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:37,280
My home is gone.

262
00:14:37,840 --> 00:14:39,040
This is still usable.

263
00:14:46,440 --> 00:14:47,360
Brother.

264
00:14:48,160 --> 00:14:49,240
How do I get to the Luo Family?

265
00:14:49,240 --> 00:14:50,100
The Luo Family?

266
00:14:50,520 --> 00:14:51,580
Go straight ahead.

267
00:14:51,880 --> 00:14:53,480
But their house was blown up.

268
00:14:53,600 --> 00:14:54,640
Thank you.

269
00:14:58,720 --> 00:15:00,920
My home is completely gone.

270
00:15:03,160 --> 00:15:05,160
It's all gone.

271
00:15:21,760 --> 00:15:22,680
Miss.

272
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:26,880
Miss.

273
00:15:27,480 --> 00:15:28,360
Miss.

274
00:15:28,960 --> 00:15:30,220
Is this the Luo Family?

275
00:15:31,040 --> 00:15:31,840
This is the Yu Family.

276
00:15:31,840 --> 00:15:33,440
The Luo Family is over there.

277
00:15:33,560 --> 00:15:34,890
It's blown up like this.

278
00:15:35,120 --> 00:15:36,960
Are the Luos okay?

279
00:15:37,120 --> 00:15:37,720
They...

280
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:39,200
Fortunately, they weren't home during the bombing.

281
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:40,800
They are all at the hotel now.

282
00:15:46,520 --> 00:15:48,760
Miss, how do I get to the hotel?

283
00:15:49,160 --> 00:15:50,120
Go straight from here.

284
00:15:50,120 --> 00:15:51,040
Then turn right at the intersection ahead.

285
00:15:51,040 --> 00:15:52,120
You'll see Han River Hotel right there.

286
00:15:52,120 --> 00:15:52,760
Thank you.

287
00:15:55,720 --> 00:15:56,780
May I ask your name?

288
00:15:59,240 --> 00:16:01,370
My surname is Zhang. I'm Zhang Yunkui.

289
00:16:01,600 --> 00:16:02,640
Zhang Yunkui?

290
00:16:10,040 --> 00:16:13,200
Are you the brigade commander of the 87th Brigade?

291
00:16:21,520 --> 00:16:22,400
Yes.

292
00:16:22,800 --> 00:16:26,000
I am Zhang Yunkui, Brigade Commander of the 87th Brigade.

293
00:16:26,680 --> 00:16:28,140
Brigade Commander Zhang.

294
00:16:28,280 --> 00:16:30,760
Where are the other brothers of the 87th Brigade?

295
00:16:30,760 --> 00:16:31,920
Why do you ask?

296
00:16:32,120 --> 00:16:33,380
I'm looking for my man.

297
00:16:35,680 --> 00:16:36,610
What's his name?

298
00:16:36,680 --> 00:16:37,400
Meng Wanfu.

299
00:16:37,960 --> 00:16:39,960
He is a soldier in your 87th Brigade.

300
00:16:40,240 --> 00:16:41,200
He's your soldier.

301
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:42,330
Do you remember him?

302
00:16:43,720 --> 00:16:45,280
Meng Wanfu?

303
00:16:47,640 --> 00:16:49,080
I don't recall that name.

304
00:16:49,120 --> 00:16:50,600
How could you not remember?

305
00:16:50,600 --> 00:16:52,600
He told me he was in the 87th Brigade.

306
00:16:52,760 --> 00:16:53,820
He is your soldier.

307
00:16:54,080 --> 00:16:55,360
Think carefully.

308
00:16:55,840 --> 00:16:56,840
I'm sorry, Miss.

309
00:16:57,160 --> 00:16:59,490
I really don't have this person around me.

310
00:17:00,560 --> 00:17:01,820
His name is Meng Wanfu.

311
00:17:02,120 --> 00:17:03,000
He's not tall.

312
00:17:03,440 --> 00:17:04,480
He has small eyes.

313
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:06,240
But they are very bright.

314
00:17:06,240 --> 00:17:07,599
He always likes to joke around.

315
00:17:07,599 --> 00:17:09,720
He said he was an orderly.

316
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:11,160
Do you remember

317
00:17:11,760 --> 00:17:13,160
during the Battle of Shanghai,

318
00:17:13,160 --> 00:17:14,960
a performance troupe went to visit?

319
00:17:14,960 --> 00:17:15,760
Do you remember?

320
00:17:15,760 --> 00:17:16,400
I remember.

321
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:17,119
I was in it.

322
00:17:17,400 --> 00:17:19,079
That was when my man and I

323
00:17:19,280 --> 00:17:20,480
met for the last time.

324
00:17:23,319 --> 00:17:24,079
Miss.

325
00:17:24,319 --> 00:17:26,119
Our brigade had 6,000 brothers.

326
00:17:26,240 --> 00:17:28,240
Each of them had their own name.

327
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:31,400
But I can name no more than a hundred of them.

328
00:17:32,160 --> 00:17:33,160
I am truly sorry.

329
00:17:33,640 --> 00:17:35,320
I didn't bring them back.

330
00:17:36,120 --> 00:17:37,480
They...

331
00:17:40,880 --> 00:17:42,560
They all died for our country.

332
00:17:58,040 --> 00:18:00,320
How can you be like this?

333
00:18:00,920 --> 00:18:03,160
That was a living human life.

334
00:18:03,280 --> 00:18:04,480
Gone just like that.

335
00:18:04,800 --> 00:18:06,800
You don't know anything when asked.

336
00:18:07,120 --> 00:18:08,980
With a simple 'I don't remember',

337
00:18:09,280 --> 00:18:10,360
you brushed it off.

338
00:18:10,640 --> 00:18:13,500
Are they just cannon fodder as you people call them?

339
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:14,460
The newspapers

340
00:18:14,600 --> 00:18:15,560
said you disobeyed orders,

341
00:18:15,560 --> 00:18:16,960
and that they were deserters.

342
00:18:16,960 --> 00:18:18,960
But they all died.

343
00:18:19,080 --> 00:18:21,560
Yet you, the brigade commander, came back alive.

344
00:18:21,560 --> 00:18:23,240
Alive to look for your family.

345
00:18:23,640 --> 00:18:25,500
You don't know anything I ask you.

346
00:18:25,520 --> 00:18:27,000
Then what exactly do you know?

347
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:28,360
What do you know?

348
00:19:08,680 --> 00:19:09,640
Miss,

349
00:19:10,560 --> 00:19:11,880
before today,

350
00:19:12,520 --> 00:19:14,440
I didn't know your man's name.

351
00:19:14,960 --> 00:19:16,120
But after today,

352
00:19:16,960 --> 00:19:18,520
I will remember.

353
00:19:18,840 --> 00:19:20,440
Meng Wanfu.

354
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:22,600
He is my brother.

355
00:19:23,680 --> 00:19:25,240
My brother forever.

356
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:27,660
Meng Wanfu was not a deserter.

357
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:29,360
They died in battle.

358
00:19:29,560 --> 00:19:32,600
They were brave warriors who killed Japanese on the battlefield.

359
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:34,920
He and those six thousand brothers

360
00:19:35,400 --> 00:19:37,400
all sacrificed their lives for the country.

361
00:19:37,400 --> 00:19:38,280
They

362
00:19:39,960 --> 00:19:42,320
are national heroes.

363
00:19:44,640 --> 00:19:46,440
They are not deserters,

364
00:19:47,120 --> 00:19:49,320
they are heroes.

365
00:19:52,880 --> 00:19:54,440
Yunkui.

366
00:19:55,840 --> 00:19:56,800
Brother.

367
00:19:57,120 --> 00:19:57,800
Zuliang.

368
00:19:59,200 --> 00:20:00,330
You're still alive.

369
00:20:00,600 --> 00:20:01,680
That's great.

370
00:20:09,120 --> 00:20:09,960
Brother.

371
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:12,200
That's great.

372
00:20:12,200 --> 00:20:13,530
Alive. We're all alive.

373
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:16,200
We're all alive.

374
00:20:21,920 --> 00:20:23,780
Our home was bombed into nothing.

375
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:28,200
The place where I grew up.

376
00:20:28,640 --> 00:20:30,770
I couldn't help but come back to see it.

377
00:20:30,800 --> 00:20:32,440
I don't even know what I wanted to see.

378
00:20:32,440 --> 00:20:34,570
I don't even know what I wanted to find.

379
00:20:34,600 --> 00:20:35,920
I just wanted to see it.

380
00:20:37,280 --> 00:20:38,600
I understand.

381
00:20:39,720 --> 00:20:41,380
Are Uncle and Aunt doing well?

382
00:20:41,720 --> 00:20:42,600
They are fine.

383
00:20:42,720 --> 00:20:44,320
They are in a hotel nearby.

384
00:20:45,280 --> 00:20:46,840
Then my father and Yujiao are here too.

385
00:20:46,840 --> 00:20:48,360
Are they doing well?

386
00:20:51,040 --> 00:20:52,200
Yunkui,

387
00:20:52,800 --> 00:20:53,960
all this time,

388
00:20:54,440 --> 00:20:55,680
where have you been?

389
00:20:56,200 --> 00:20:58,530
Did you not hear any news about them at all?

390
00:20:59,280 --> 00:21:00,520
What news?

391
00:21:02,720 --> 00:21:04,120
Uncle and Sister-in-law

392
00:21:04,920 --> 00:21:07,000
had an accident on their way to Wuhan.

393
00:21:07,920 --> 00:21:09,520
The Japanese bombed Nanjing

394
00:21:09,680 --> 00:21:10,880
and sank the Meiyun.

395
00:21:11,200 --> 00:21:12,560
When the ship was bombed,

396
00:21:12,560 --> 00:21:14,360
it was in the middle of the river.

397
00:21:15,160 --> 00:21:16,720
No one survived.

398
00:21:18,080 --> 00:21:19,200
Uncle and Sister-in-law

399
00:21:19,200 --> 00:21:21,330
are on the list of missing passengers.

400
00:21:35,440 --> 00:21:38,040
Brother, cry if you want to.

401
00:22:12,320 --> 00:22:13,240
Yunkui.

402
00:22:28,080 --> 00:22:28,800
Brother.

403
00:22:44,640 --> 00:22:45,570
Four Treasures.

404
00:22:46,720 --> 00:22:47,520
Butler Zhu.

405
00:22:47,840 --> 00:22:48,720
Let me ask you,

406
00:22:49,040 --> 00:22:50,500
since Wanfu has been here,

407
00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:51,800
what did Mr. Tian say?

408
00:22:52,160 --> 00:22:53,600
Is he satisfied with the food?

409
00:22:53,600 --> 00:22:55,840
I can't tell for lunch and dinner.

410
00:22:56,240 --> 00:22:58,640
Most of the time, Sir lets the kitchen decide.

411
00:22:58,640 --> 00:23:00,040
But for breakfast, he's been eating

412
00:23:00,040 --> 00:23:01,570
Baozi for many days in a row.

413
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:04,200
Really?

414
00:23:05,120 --> 00:23:05,920
It's nothing.

415
00:23:06,200 --> 00:23:07,130
Get back to work.

416
00:23:07,720 --> 00:23:08,600
Head Steward.

417
00:23:09,920 --> 00:23:10,640
Miss Sibao.

418
00:23:10,800 --> 00:23:11,600
Mrs. Meng.

419
00:23:12,400 --> 00:23:13,200
Butler Zhu.

420
00:23:13,600 --> 00:23:14,560
Mrs. Meng.

421
00:23:15,080 --> 00:23:17,280
I picked some dandelions in the garden.

422
00:23:17,400 --> 00:23:18,720
Dandelion tea made this season

423
00:23:18,720 --> 00:23:20,040
tastes the best.

424
00:23:20,280 --> 00:23:22,000
First, steam them over high heat,

425
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:23,280
then stir-fry them over low heat.

426
00:23:23,280 --> 00:23:24,480
I only made this much.

427
00:23:24,520 --> 00:23:25,600
I gave half to my father,

428
00:23:25,600 --> 00:23:28,400
and I hope you won't mind taking the other half.

429
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:33,160
Dandelions?

430
00:23:34,080 --> 00:23:35,560
That's the first time I've heard of that.

431
00:23:35,560 --> 00:23:37,920
Dandelion tea is great for cooling and detoxifying.

432
00:23:37,920 --> 00:23:40,120
You manage so many things in the mansion.

433
00:23:40,120 --> 00:23:41,560
You should take care of your health.

434
00:23:41,560 --> 00:23:42,400
Please try it first.

435
00:23:42,400 --> 00:23:43,200
If you like it,

436
00:23:43,360 --> 00:23:45,160
I'll prepare more for you later.

437
00:23:45,680 --> 00:23:46,720
Mrs. Meng.

438
00:23:47,600 --> 00:23:49,640
Do you need a favor from me?

439
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:51,160
Just say it.

440
00:23:53,360 --> 00:23:54,120
Then,

441
00:23:54,840 --> 00:23:56,360
I'll just say it.

442
00:23:57,920 --> 00:23:59,050
Could I trouble you?

443
00:23:59,200 --> 00:24:01,720
Assign me some chores in the house.

444
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:04,060
I don't need wages.

445
00:24:04,240 --> 00:24:05,760
As long as you let me and my father

446
00:24:05,760 --> 00:24:07,240
eat with the servants in the house,

447
00:24:07,240 --> 00:24:08,240
that'll be fine.

448
00:24:10,160 --> 00:24:11,120
What can you do?

449
00:24:11,240 --> 00:24:12,480
I can do anything.

450
00:24:13,160 --> 00:24:14,420
I can endure hardship.

451
00:24:22,880 --> 00:24:26,120
This smell is quite special.

452
00:24:28,360 --> 00:24:29,280
Sibao.

453
00:24:30,680 --> 00:24:33,140
When you're too busy with work in the future,

454
00:24:33,360 --> 00:24:35,240
ask Mrs. Meng to help you.

455
00:24:35,720 --> 00:24:36,400
Okay.

456
00:24:36,680 --> 00:24:38,040
Thank you, Butler Zhu.

457
00:24:43,560 --> 00:24:45,200
Then I'll leave Miss Sibao in your care.

458
00:24:45,200 --> 00:24:46,000
It's nothing.

459
00:24:46,320 --> 00:24:47,200
Is there anything else to wash?

460
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:47,840
Let me help you.

461
00:24:47,840 --> 00:24:49,200
It's fine. I just need to hang them up.

462
00:24:49,200 --> 00:24:49,800
Okay.

463
00:24:51,280 --> 00:24:52,840
If there's anything else in the house,

464
00:24:52,840 --> 00:24:53,760
I'll call you.

465
00:24:53,960 --> 00:24:54,680
Sure.

466
00:24:54,920 --> 00:24:55,920
If there's anything,

467
00:24:55,920 --> 00:24:56,960
as long as I can help,

468
00:24:56,960 --> 00:24:57,720
just call me.

469
00:24:58,000 --> 00:24:58,800
Okay.

470
00:25:21,920 --> 00:25:22,480
Hello, Chef Jiao.

471
00:25:22,480 --> 00:25:23,480
Hello, Chef Jiao.

472
00:25:30,520 --> 00:25:31,520
Hello, Chef Jiao.

473
00:25:35,760 --> 00:25:36,840
What are you doing?

474
00:25:37,080 --> 00:25:38,240
Stop.

475
00:25:38,640 --> 00:25:40,160
What are you cutting?

476
00:25:40,280 --> 00:25:43,120
If people didn't know better, they'd think you were cutting taro strips.

477
00:25:43,120 --> 00:25:43,640
No,

478
00:25:43,720 --> 00:25:46,520
aren't you making that Assorted Tofu Soup?

479
00:25:48,280 --> 00:25:50,800
Assorted Tofu Soup is also called Wensi Tofu.

480
00:25:50,800 --> 00:25:52,360
Shred the tofu in one go.

481
00:25:52,480 --> 00:25:54,080
You can't stop in the middle.

482
00:25:54,400 --> 00:25:56,800
Besides keeping the shape of the shredded tofu,

483
00:25:56,800 --> 00:25:58,960
each shred must be as thin as a hair.

484
00:25:59,280 --> 00:26:02,120
That way, the chicken soup can be absorbed well.

485
00:26:02,320 --> 00:26:03,920
Look at what you're cutting.

486
00:26:04,320 --> 00:26:05,520
It looks like fingers.

487
00:26:05,520 --> 00:26:07,640
I don't care how you cut it in Shandong.

488
00:26:07,640 --> 00:26:09,280
But don't forget this is Shanghai.

489
00:26:09,280 --> 00:26:11,680
You want to be a chef with your knife skills?

490
00:26:11,920 --> 00:26:13,640
What a waste of ingredients.

491
00:26:14,760 --> 00:26:15,600
Cut it again.

492
00:26:15,760 --> 00:26:18,960
The wasted ingredients will be deducted from your wages.

493
00:26:24,520 --> 00:26:25,120
Chef Jiao.

494
00:26:26,320 --> 00:26:27,720
Is everything prepared?

495
00:26:28,240 --> 00:26:29,040
Miss Sibao.

496
00:26:29,440 --> 00:26:30,040
What's up?

497
00:26:30,160 --> 00:26:31,720
Are you ordering food today?

498
00:26:31,720 --> 00:26:33,680
I want the Sweet and Sour Yellow River Carp from the other day

499
00:26:33,680 --> 00:26:35,410
and Braised Tofu with Seafood.

500
00:26:38,400 --> 00:26:39,040
Got it.

501
00:26:40,880 --> 00:26:41,480
Wanfu.

502
00:26:42,280 --> 00:26:43,880
Finish cutting this Wensi Tofu,

503
00:26:43,880 --> 00:26:45,920
and clean up your Yellow River carp.

504
00:26:46,920 --> 00:26:47,720
Got it.

505
00:26:48,320 --> 00:26:49,200
Fugui.

506
00:26:49,920 --> 00:26:51,640
After this, take out the sea cucumber.

507
00:26:51,640 --> 00:26:52,160
Okay.

508
00:26:52,200 --> 00:26:52,800
Lao Guo.

509
00:26:53,360 --> 00:26:54,120
Chef Jiao.

510
00:26:54,280 --> 00:26:56,640
Check if the conchs have spit out all the sand.

511
00:26:56,640 --> 00:26:57,800
Okay, don't worry.

512
00:26:58,000 --> 00:26:58,600
Douzi.

513
00:26:59,360 --> 00:27:00,280
Coming.

514
00:27:07,040 --> 00:27:07,640
Brother Wanfu.

515
00:27:07,640 --> 00:27:09,640
You cut the shredded tofu so finely.

516
00:27:10,320 --> 00:27:11,160
Not bad.

517
00:27:11,320 --> 00:27:11,840
By the way, Wanfu,

518
00:27:11,840 --> 00:27:13,600
the baozi you steamed this morning were really delicious.

519
00:27:13,600 --> 00:27:14,360
Really?

520
00:27:14,680 --> 00:27:15,610
If you like them,

521
00:27:15,720 --> 00:27:16,840
next time I steam some,

522
00:27:16,840 --> 00:27:18,440
I'll make a few extra for you.

523
00:27:18,520 --> 00:27:19,680
Great!

524
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:21,560
Mrs. Meng is so lucky.

525
00:27:22,960 --> 00:27:24,560
What are you chatting about?

526
00:27:25,040 --> 00:27:27,120
Your spit is getting into the food.

527
00:27:29,600 --> 00:27:30,920
That Yellow River carp

528
00:27:31,720 --> 00:27:33,280
is the main dish.

529
00:27:55,120 --> 00:27:56,720
Xiaoyue, congratulations.

530
00:27:56,800 --> 00:27:57,960
You passed the assessment.

531
00:27:57,960 --> 00:27:59,320
You are now a real nurse.

532
00:28:00,000 --> 00:28:01,200
Learn from Nurse Sun.

533
00:28:01,240 --> 00:28:02,400
She has a lot of experience.

534
00:28:02,400 --> 00:28:03,840
Okay, Young Master Luo.

535
00:28:05,080 --> 00:28:06,540
Call me Dr. Luo from now on.

536
00:28:06,840 --> 00:28:08,320
Yes, Dr. Luo.

537
00:28:10,080 --> 00:28:11,040
Let's go, Xiaoyue.

538
00:28:11,040 --> 00:28:12,240
Come with me to do the rounds.

539
00:28:12,240 --> 00:28:13,000
Okay.

540
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:19,060
Squad Leader Wang.

541
00:28:19,120 --> 00:28:20,360
How many times have I told you?

542
00:28:20,360 --> 00:28:22,020
Get out of bed and walk around.

543
00:28:22,040 --> 00:28:22,760
You just had surgery.

544
00:28:22,760 --> 00:28:23,760
You need to prevent intestinal adhesions.

545
00:28:23,760 --> 00:28:25,080
It's for your own good, okay?

546
00:28:25,080 --> 00:28:26,340
It's for your own good.

547
00:28:27,120 --> 00:28:27,960
Pan.

548
00:28:28,280 --> 00:28:29,360
How are you today?

549
00:28:30,200 --> 00:28:31,260
Does it still hurt?

550
00:28:32,160 --> 00:28:33,160
Let me take a look.

551
00:28:36,080 --> 00:28:37,040
Your wound...

552
00:28:38,320 --> 00:28:39,720
Why is it infected again?

553
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:41,200
Keep it away from water.

554
00:28:41,200 --> 00:28:41,960
You know?

555
00:28:46,800 --> 00:28:49,160
Has he been in a coma like this the whole time?

556
00:28:49,160 --> 00:28:50,200
Do you know him?

557
00:28:50,440 --> 00:28:52,170
I heard he used to be an officer.

558
00:28:52,400 --> 00:28:54,640
He is covered in old wounds.

559
00:28:55,240 --> 00:28:57,370
Several of these wounds are infected.

560
00:28:58,160 --> 00:28:59,800
Antibiotics aren't working.

561
00:28:59,800 --> 00:29:01,320
Dr. Luo is worried

562
00:29:01,440 --> 00:29:03,400
he might die from organ failure,

563
00:29:04,520 --> 00:29:06,520
so he arranged special care for him.

564
00:29:09,280 --> 00:29:11,410
He hasn't been in a coma the whole time.

565
00:29:11,640 --> 00:29:12,900
Sometimes he wakes up,

566
00:29:13,120 --> 00:29:14,280
looks outside,

567
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:15,490
and stares blankly.

568
00:29:16,240 --> 00:29:17,640
Last night, he even lost his temper

569
00:29:17,640 --> 00:29:19,120
with Dr. Luo.

570
00:29:19,440 --> 00:29:20,400
Nurse Sun.

571
00:29:21,320 --> 00:29:22,980
I think my wound has opened up.

572
00:29:23,400 --> 00:29:24,730
Okay, let me take a look.

573
00:29:24,800 --> 00:29:26,000
You keep an eye on him.

574
00:31:30,640 --> 00:31:32,400
Dr. Luo, time to eat.

575
00:31:32,760 --> 00:31:33,720
Xiaoyue.

576
00:31:39,320 --> 00:31:40,200
Xiaoyue.

577
00:31:40,400 --> 00:31:42,160
When you deliver food to the wounded later,

578
00:31:42,160 --> 00:31:43,960
give these two eggs to my cousin.

579
00:31:45,080 --> 00:31:47,080
I won't go. Go yourself.

580
00:31:47,760 --> 00:31:48,680
What's wrong?

581
00:31:50,240 --> 00:31:52,280
What's the deal with Zhang Yunkui?

582
00:31:52,840 --> 00:31:54,280
He's really weird.

583
00:31:55,320 --> 00:31:56,520
Don't misunderstand.

584
00:31:56,520 --> 00:31:57,400
He's suffering from mental trauma and a gunshot wound.

585
00:31:57,400 --> 00:31:59,080
Both are afflicting him at once,

586
00:31:59,080 --> 00:32:00,480
so it's understandable.

587
00:32:00,520 --> 00:32:02,240
He doesn't have mental trauma.

588
00:32:02,240 --> 00:32:03,770
He has a guilty conscience.

589
00:32:04,080 --> 00:32:05,040
Looking at him,

590
00:32:05,200 --> 00:32:07,080
the runaway general rumor is probably true.

591
00:32:07,080 --> 00:32:09,400
The runaway general was a false accusation by his superior.

592
00:32:09,400 --> 00:32:11,060
He could have sought justice,

593
00:32:11,320 --> 00:32:12,600
but for the sake of the country

594
00:32:12,600 --> 00:32:15,720
and the pensions of all the soldiers in the 87th Brigade,

595
00:32:15,720 --> 00:32:17,180
he gave up his reputation,

596
00:32:17,320 --> 00:32:18,480
and even his name.

597
00:32:18,880 --> 00:32:19,760
At this time,

598
00:32:19,960 --> 00:32:21,240
I also told him

599
00:32:21,680 --> 00:32:22,940
that his father, wife,

600
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:24,040
and unborn child

601
00:32:24,120 --> 00:32:25,250
had all been killed.

602
00:32:25,840 --> 00:32:27,440
I can cure his gunshot wound,

603
00:32:27,640 --> 00:32:29,680
but I can't cure his mental trauma.

604
00:32:40,800 --> 00:32:42,160
Dr. Luo.

605
00:32:52,520 --> 00:32:53,600
Come, time to eat.

606
00:32:54,320 --> 00:32:56,240
His hands are injured, I'll get it for him.

607
00:32:56,240 --> 00:32:57,440
Brother, time to eat.

608
00:32:57,720 --> 00:32:58,450
Is it enough?

609
00:32:58,480 --> 00:32:59,280
Time to eat.

610
00:33:01,880 --> 00:33:02,680
A bit more.

611
00:33:02,760 --> 00:33:04,360
His injuries are too severe.

612
00:33:05,320 --> 00:33:06,520
Thank you, Nurse Han.

613
00:33:08,440 --> 00:33:10,240
Eat, there's nothing else here.

614
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:23,400
These are the eggs Dr. Luo saved

615
00:33:23,400 --> 00:33:24,480
for you.

616
00:33:24,520 --> 00:33:26,520
Be discreet when eating them later.

617
00:33:30,200 --> 00:33:30,880
Here.

618
00:33:40,160 --> 00:33:41,440
On the battlefield,

619
00:33:41,960 --> 00:33:43,160
I ate worse than a pig.

620
00:33:43,920 --> 00:33:45,850
I didn't expect this hospital food

621
00:33:46,360 --> 00:33:47,680
to be just clear broth.

622
00:33:48,080 --> 00:33:51,120
How much porridge do you have to eat to heal this injury?

623
00:33:51,120 --> 00:33:52,440
It's too severe.

624
00:33:59,520 --> 00:34:00,400
Brother.

625
00:34:01,480 --> 00:34:02,400
He has eggs.

626
00:34:03,440 --> 00:34:04,120
Eggs?

627
00:34:04,360 --> 00:34:04,960
Where are the eggs?

628
00:34:04,960 --> 00:34:06,040
Eggs? Where?

629
00:34:06,320 --> 00:34:07,280
Where are the eggs?

630
00:34:07,280 --> 00:34:07,960
Where are the eggs?

631
00:34:07,960 --> 00:34:08,639
Where did the eggs come from?

632
00:34:08,639 --> 00:34:09,239
Where are the eggs?

633
00:34:09,239 --> 00:34:10,600
Brother, where are the eggs?

634
00:34:10,600 --> 00:34:11,159
Here.

635
00:34:11,400 --> 00:34:12,280
There really are eggs.

636
00:34:12,280 --> 00:34:13,679
There actually are eggs.

637
00:34:15,040 --> 00:34:16,199
Nurse Han.

638
00:34:16,239 --> 00:34:16,920
Nurse Han.

639
00:34:16,920 --> 00:34:18,120
Nurse Zhang.

640
00:34:18,760 --> 00:34:19,679
Nurse Zhang.

641
00:34:19,800 --> 00:34:20,719
Did you forget

642
00:34:20,760 --> 00:34:21,880
to hand out our eggs?

643
00:34:21,880 --> 00:34:22,400
Nurse Zhang.

644
00:34:22,400 --> 00:34:23,330
What's going on?

645
00:34:23,560 --> 00:34:24,360
Where are our eggs?

646
00:34:24,360 --> 00:34:25,040
Where is my egg?

647
00:34:25,040 --> 00:34:25,719
My leg is injured too,

648
00:34:25,719 --> 00:34:26,880
give me an egg to nourish it.

649
00:34:26,880 --> 00:34:28,040
When has our hospital's food

650
00:34:28,040 --> 00:34:29,170
ever included eggs?

651
00:34:29,560 --> 00:34:30,020
No eggs.

652
00:34:30,080 --> 00:34:31,739
Then where did he get his eggs?

653
00:34:32,120 --> 00:34:32,800
There are eggs!

654
00:34:32,800 --> 00:34:33,840
How would I know?

655
00:34:34,120 --> 00:34:34,880
You don't know?

656
00:34:34,880 --> 00:34:36,080
Then where did the egg come from?

657
00:34:36,080 --> 00:34:36,600
Exactly.

658
00:34:36,600 --> 00:34:37,330
He has an egg.

659
00:34:37,520 --> 00:34:38,320
He has an egg.

660
00:34:38,639 --> 00:34:39,239
Yeah.

661
00:34:42,239 --> 00:34:45,159
Brother, is the egg delicious?

662
00:34:49,400 --> 00:34:50,659
Where did it come from?

663
00:34:55,920 --> 00:34:57,280
I'm asking you.

664
00:34:57,600 --> 00:34:59,440
Are you looking down on me?

665
00:35:00,640 --> 00:35:01,570
I'll let you eat!

666
00:35:02,840 --> 00:35:03,970
Look down on me, huh?

667
00:35:04,600 --> 00:35:06,240
Keeping it all to yourself, huh?

668
00:35:06,240 --> 00:35:07,120
Look down on me, huh?

669
00:35:07,120 --> 00:35:07,800
What a waste.

670
00:35:07,800 --> 00:35:08,240
Didn't see it.

671
00:35:08,240 --> 00:35:09,560
Eat it.

672
00:35:10,240 --> 00:35:11,200
Give me the egg.

673
00:35:11,800 --> 00:35:13,120
Aren't you a big eater?

674
00:35:13,560 --> 00:35:14,960
Eat this for me.

675
00:35:16,560 --> 00:35:17,600
Eating it with the shell?

676
00:35:17,600 --> 00:35:18,560
He's actually eating it.

677
00:35:18,560 --> 00:35:19,440
Is that edible?

678
00:35:19,760 --> 00:35:21,360
Your teeth are really tough.

679
00:35:23,320 --> 00:35:24,680
Is he even normal?

680
00:35:25,880 --> 00:35:27,140
What's wrong with him?

681
00:35:28,120 --> 00:35:28,880
Here.

682
00:35:29,080 --> 00:35:30,480
I'll give you some noodles.

683
00:35:30,480 --> 00:35:32,140
This is much better than eggs.

684
00:35:32,400 --> 00:35:32,840
Here.

685
00:35:32,880 --> 00:35:33,480
That's gauze.

686
00:35:33,480 --> 00:35:34,010
Eat it up.

687
00:35:34,080 --> 00:35:35,080
This is bullying.

688
00:35:35,440 --> 00:35:36,440
Isn't it too much?

689
00:35:36,440 --> 00:35:37,160
Eat.

690
00:35:37,360 --> 00:35:38,240
What are you doing?

691
00:35:38,240 --> 00:35:39,680
Brother, Nurse Han is here.

692
00:35:39,680 --> 00:35:40,340
Move aside.

693
00:35:43,280 --> 00:35:44,320
Are you stupid?

694
00:35:44,560 --> 00:35:46,520
This is gauze. Can you eat this?

695
00:35:46,520 --> 00:35:47,400
He swallowed it all.

696
00:35:47,400 --> 00:35:48,280
Will he be okay?

697
00:35:54,360 --> 00:35:55,760
Why are there eggshells?

698
00:35:59,160 --> 00:36:00,120
You just eat whatever

699
00:36:00,120 --> 00:36:01,080
others give you?

700
00:36:01,120 --> 00:36:02,440
Don't you have a brain?

701
00:36:02,520 --> 00:36:03,800
Nurse Han.

702
00:36:04,600 --> 00:36:05,880
Why does he have an egg?

703
00:36:06,160 --> 00:36:07,160
We don't have any.

704
00:36:07,240 --> 00:36:08,640
Yeah, we want eggs too.

705
00:36:08,920 --> 00:36:11,180
Who can stand eating porridge every day?

706
00:36:11,800 --> 00:36:12,320
He has an egg.

707
00:36:12,320 --> 00:36:13,960
You are all brothers wounded in battle.

708
00:36:13,960 --> 00:36:15,840
How could you bully someone like this?

709
00:36:15,840 --> 00:36:17,080
So what if I bullied him?

710
00:36:17,080 --> 00:36:18,160
Who told him to keep it all to himself?

711
00:36:18,160 --> 00:36:19,520
Yeah, we want to eat eggs too.

712
00:36:19,520 --> 00:36:20,280
Give us some.

713
00:36:20,280 --> 00:36:21,040
We haven't eaten eggs either.

714
00:36:21,040 --> 00:36:21,960
We want eggs too.

715
00:36:21,960 --> 00:36:23,620
Dr. Luo prepared this for him.

716
00:36:23,640 --> 00:36:24,800
He brought it from home.

717
00:36:24,800 --> 00:36:25,880
It's not hospital food.

718
00:36:25,880 --> 00:36:26,810
Dr. Luo has eggs?

719
00:36:27,000 --> 00:36:28,040
Then let's go find Dr. Luo.

720
00:36:28,040 --> 00:36:29,320
Let's go find Dr. Luo.

721
00:36:29,440 --> 00:36:31,080
You can't even make up a good story.

722
00:36:31,080 --> 00:36:32,080
If Dr. Luo is so nice,

723
00:36:32,080 --> 00:36:34,480
bring me an egg next time.

724
00:36:34,560 --> 00:36:35,960
Look at the wound on my head.

725
00:36:35,960 --> 00:36:36,960
Isn't it much worse than his?

726
00:36:36,960 --> 00:36:38,000
Yeah, look at my arm.

727
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:39,120
Brother, I'm injured too, look.

728
00:36:39,120 --> 00:36:40,880
Seriously injured but still beating people.

729
00:36:40,880 --> 00:36:42,400
If you are healed and have too much energy,

730
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:44,040
go back to the battlefield and fight the Japanese!

731
00:36:44,040 --> 00:36:45,680
I want to fight the Japanese too,

732
00:36:45,680 --> 00:36:47,540
but my head injury hasn't healed.

733
00:36:47,840 --> 00:36:49,440
How can I have the strength to fight them?

734
00:36:49,440 --> 00:36:50,800
That's why we need to nourish ourselves.

735
00:36:50,800 --> 00:36:51,680
Nourish what?

736
00:36:51,960 --> 00:36:53,820
So you can beat your own brothers?

737
00:37:22,600 --> 00:37:24,680
You are a brigade commander after all.

738
00:37:24,680 --> 00:37:27,140
How can you let them humiliate you like this?

739
00:37:41,360 --> 00:37:43,160
I know you feel awful,

740
00:37:44,000 --> 00:37:45,960
but bottling it up won't help.

741
00:37:49,600 --> 00:37:51,660
When I found out Wanfu died in battle,

742
00:37:54,160 --> 00:37:56,420
I was so heartbroken I couldn't even cry.

743
00:37:57,000 --> 00:37:58,560
I just couldn't believe it.

744
00:37:59,200 --> 00:38:01,560
How could someone as clever as Wanfu

745
00:38:02,920 --> 00:38:04,120
be gone?

746
00:38:06,200 --> 00:38:07,920
Later, I set up a grave for him.

747
00:38:08,960 --> 00:38:11,000
After I went back, I cried my eyes out.

748
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:12,800
I cried for three days straight.

749
00:38:13,760 --> 00:38:15,120
Crying has one benefit.

750
00:38:15,680 --> 00:38:18,410
Once you let it out, you won't feel so suffocated.

751
00:38:19,120 --> 00:38:20,920
If you have any pain, just say it.

752
00:38:21,880 --> 00:38:23,480
Or just have a good cry.

753
00:38:35,400 --> 00:38:37,320
The dead are gone.

754
00:38:38,000 --> 00:38:40,080
The living must live on well.

755
00:38:40,520 --> 00:38:42,650
You can't torture yourself like this.

756
00:38:42,840 --> 00:38:45,600
If others tell you to eat unpeeled eggs, you eat them.

757
00:38:45,600 --> 00:38:47,280
If they tell you to eat gauze, you eat it.

758
00:38:47,280 --> 00:38:49,280
You eat whatever others tell you to.

759
00:38:53,920 --> 00:38:55,240
Would you eat grass?

760
00:39:03,640 --> 00:39:04,840
Did you see clearly?

761
00:39:05,080 --> 00:39:06,960
This is grass. Can you eat it?

762
00:39:07,200 --> 00:39:08,200
Spit it out.

763
00:39:10,160 --> 00:39:11,160
Spit it out.

764
00:39:11,800 --> 00:39:13,860
Aren't you afraid of being poisoned?

765
00:39:18,640 --> 00:39:20,720
Zhang Yunkui, is there something wrong with you?

766
00:39:20,720 --> 00:39:21,840
No one feels good

767
00:39:21,960 --> 00:39:23,800
after coming off the battlefield.

768
00:39:23,800 --> 00:39:25,400
Now I know why the men of the 87th Brigade

769
00:39:25,400 --> 00:39:26,720
all died in your hands.

770
00:39:26,760 --> 00:39:28,040
With a jerk like you,

771
00:39:28,080 --> 00:39:29,280
it's hard to survive.

772
00:39:29,680 --> 00:39:32,080
I really feel it was unworthy for our Wanfu.

773
00:39:39,120 --> 00:39:40,120
Zhang Yunkui.

774
00:39:40,280 --> 00:39:41,760
You are a big idiot.

775
00:39:41,960 --> 00:39:43,560
Go eat your grass.

776
00:41:18,080 --> 00:41:18,960
Wanfu.

777
00:41:20,240 --> 00:41:22,560
The color of your broth is wrong.

778
00:41:22,920 --> 00:41:23,980
The heat is too low.

779
00:41:24,360 --> 00:41:25,400
Turn it up.

780
00:41:25,920 --> 00:41:26,850
Well, Chef Jiao.

781
00:41:27,200 --> 00:41:28,240
For this fish soup,

782
00:41:28,240 --> 00:41:30,240
aren't you supposed to use high heat when making the broth,

783
00:41:30,240 --> 00:41:31,840
and then simmer it on low heat?

784
00:41:31,840 --> 00:41:33,100
Who's the expert here?

785
00:41:35,160 --> 00:41:37,040
Okay. I'll turn it up.

786
00:41:45,160 --> 00:41:45,840
Old Jiao.

787
00:41:46,640 --> 00:41:47,300
Butler Zhu.

788
00:41:47,480 --> 00:41:50,680
Sir is going to host a few important guests these next couple of days.

789
00:41:50,680 --> 00:41:52,410
They are all renowned gourmets

790
00:41:52,520 --> 00:41:54,280
in The Bund.

791
00:41:54,920 --> 00:41:57,250
They are knowledgeable and experienced.

792
00:41:57,360 --> 00:41:59,090
You must show your best skills.

793
00:41:59,160 --> 00:42:00,720
All right. Rest assured.

794
00:42:01,880 --> 00:42:02,600
Wanfu.

795
00:42:04,080 --> 00:42:06,680
You should also make a few of your specialties.

796
00:42:08,040 --> 00:42:08,700
Butler Zhu.

797
00:42:08,920 --> 00:42:11,040
He only makes home-style dishes.

798
00:42:11,200 --> 00:42:12,800
They can't be served at a formal banquet.

799
00:42:12,800 --> 00:42:15,520
What kind of banquets haven't these guests had?

800
00:42:15,960 --> 00:42:16,820
How about this?

801
00:42:17,280 --> 00:42:19,840
You two will each make four main courses,

802
00:42:19,960 --> 00:42:20,520
one soup,

803
00:42:20,640 --> 00:42:21,560
and one dessert.

804
00:42:21,560 --> 00:42:23,120
Whoever cooks the most exquisitely

805
00:42:23,120 --> 00:42:24,380
and is the most popular

806
00:42:24,640 --> 00:42:26,640
will be rewarded with ten silver dollars.

807
00:42:26,640 --> 00:42:28,040
Think it over carefully.

808
00:42:28,760 --> 00:42:29,560
Don't worry.

809
00:42:30,240 --> 00:42:30,920
Butler Zhu.

810
00:42:42,320 --> 00:42:43,250
Four Treasures.

811
00:42:44,080 --> 00:42:45,520
Do you know what kind of guests

812
00:42:45,520 --> 00:42:47,360
Mr. Tian invited?

813
00:42:52,200 --> 00:42:53,240
As for this competition,

814
00:42:53,240 --> 00:42:54,800
I must win no matter what.

815
00:42:55,040 --> 00:42:56,900
It's not just about the ten bucks.

816
00:42:57,040 --> 00:42:57,600
This is about

817
00:42:57,600 --> 00:42:59,680
the ruling power of the kitchen in the future.

818
00:42:59,680 --> 00:43:01,720
Yes, we must win.
